  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@francoischalifour Yesterday I tried to add a test for that, but it was hard to simulate user input like in real world.\r\nIn real world, we type and it adds each character at a time to input, but with testing-library, it just triggered an event with a value like '10.34'.\r\n\r\nToday I tried their [user-event](https://testing-library.com/docs/ecosystem-user-event) package which is supposed to give a better simulation.\r\nI ran\r\n\r\n```js\r\nawait userEvent.type(minInput, '10.34');\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut it triggered the following 5 events.\r\n\r\n- `1`\r\n- `10`\r\n- `10.`\r\n- `10.3`\r\n- `10.34`\r\n\r\nSo this obviously cannot cover this regression. I think it could be only possible with real e2e test like selenium or cypress.",
